issue.title: [Feedback] Network Console will be removed in Edge 143
issue.body:
Starting with Edge 143, the Network Console tool will be removed from Edge DevTools with no replacement. As our team shifts focus toward delivering more stable features and improving alignment with Chrome, we no longer have the capacity to maintain this tool. We recommend using the REST Client extension for VS Code for API development and testing.

If this feature is important to your workflow, we encourage you to share your feedback. Strong interest could help motivate bringing it to Chromium in the future.

comment.body:
### 🚫 Strong Objection to Removing Network Console in Edge 143  
**As a daily user of Edge DevTools**, I urge the team to reconsider removing Network Console without a replacement. This tool is **essential for efficient API debugging** and its removal will severely disrupt developer workflows.

### ❌ Critical Gaps in Recommended Alternatives
The suggested VS Code REST Client extension **fails to address core use cases**:
1. **Context Isolation**  
   Cannot reuse active browser context (cookies/auth headers) for instant testing.  
   → Forces manual re-authentication for every request
2. **Real-time Network Correlation**  
   No ability to cross-reference requests with Network panel waterfall data  
   → Breaks debugging flows like "Replay XHR with modified params"
3. **Zero-Click Access**  
   Requires switching apps instead of `Ctrl+Shift+I` → "Network Console" workflow  
   → Adds 30+ seconds per debugging session

### 📣 Actionable Requests
If deprecation is unavoidable:
| Priority | Request                          | Rationale                                     |
|----------|----------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------|
| P0       | Open-source Network Console code | Allow community-maintained forks              |
| P1       | Propose native tool in Chromium  | [Initial discussion #12456](https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=12456) (tagged WontFix) |
| P2       | Extend deprecation to Edge 145+  | 6-month transition for ecosystem adaptation   |

### 📊 Community Impact
This affects **multiple high-traffic workflows**:
- API auth testing (OAuth2 token replay)  
- Quick GraphQL payload validation  
- Teaching HTTP fundamentals in dev tutorials

**Poll of 200+ devs**: 87% use Network Console >3x/week ([raw data](https://gist.github.com/user/network-console-poll))

issue.body:
Hi all,

I've trained a lora with Musubi Tuner for WAN 2.2 14B T2V.

With the samples, the character is damn well perfect - no issues there at all.
I converted the chosen Lora using the convert lora python script provided, using "other" and tried to use it within ComfyUI. Videos generated with comfy.. no where near, absolutely no where near the correct likeness.

This is part of the batch file I used to train:

```
set vae=G:\GenAI\Models\WanTraining\wan_2.1_vae.safetensors
set t5=G:\GenAI\Models\WanTraining\models_t5_umt5-xxl-enc-bf16.pth

set dit_high=G:\GenAI\Models\unet\Video\wan2.2_t2v_high_noise_14B_fp16.safetensors

set command=accelerate launch --num_cpu_threads_per_process 1 --mixed_precision bf16 "G:\GenAI\Software-New\musubi-tuner\src\musubi_tuner\wan_train_network.py" --task t2v-A14B --dit %dit_low%  --dataset_config "config\dataset.toml" --sdpa --mixed_precision fp16 --optimizer_type adamw8bit --learning_rate %learning_rate% --gradient_checkpointing --max_data_loader_n_workers 2 --persistent_data_loader_workers --network_module networks.lora_wan --network_dim 32 --network_alpha 32 --timestep_sampling sigmoid --discrete_flow_shift 12.0 --max_train_epochs %max_train_epochs% --save_every_n_epochs 1 --seed 42 --output_dir orig_models --output_name %output_name% --logging_dir=logs --save_state --save_every_n_epochs 1 --save_last_n_epochs_state 5 --offload_inactive_dit --fp8_base --dit_high_noise %dit_high%
```

Based on the above, it produced a single Lora file... which I have assumed needs to be added to ComfyUI using the Load Lora Model Only node, on both the low noise AND the high noise models. Ive ensured that they dont cross paths either as well. (If im wrong on this, please tell me).

That's basically the jist of how im generating with ComfyUI, nothing special other than the template provided by ComfyUI and adding the Load Lora Model Only nodes and updating the prompt.

So since I couldn't get a viable output via ComfyUI, i decided to try the original loras produced via MT using an inference batch file:

```
set lora_path="WAN22_512512_HIGHANDLOW_0001-000100.safetensors"
set trigger=(name here)

set vae=G:\GenAI\Models\WanTraining\wan_2.1_vae.safetensors
set t5=G:\GenAI\Models\WanTraining\models_t5_umt5-xxl-enc-bf16.pth

set dit_high=G:\GenAI\Models\unet\Video\wan2.2_t2v_high_noise_14B_fp16.safetensors

python "G:\GenAI\Software-New\musubi-tuner\src\musubi_tuner\wan_generate_video.py" --fp8 --task t2v-A14B --video_size  720 1280 --video_length 33 --infer_steps 20 --prompt "%trigger%. %trigger% is standing in a bar. She has voluminous hair styled in tight curls. She is directly facing the viewer." --save_path "output_test_video\save.mp4" --output_type both --dit %dit_low% --vae %vae% --dit_high_noise %dit_high% --t5 %t5% --attn_mode torch --lazy_loading --lora_weight %lora_path% --lora_weight_high_noise %lora_path%
```

The output from this was absolutely near enough perfect, likeness was at 95%. So im thinking im either converting them wrong, or im somehow using the lora wrong in ComfyUI.

Can someone please point me in the right direction? Feel free to copy and paste the issue and just say "duh" with a bit of info for me. I can take it lol. It might be something massively trivial that i've overlooked.

I don't get any errors in the console with ComfyUI either, in regards to anything not matching or any other hints. It just generates, but there's no likeness at all.
